opensciences is seems to be taken its roots in kenya at a very good pace as kenyans are really advocating for open data in research through social media such as facebook and twitter
in facebook which is main social media used by majority of people in the wolrd has played a great role in creating awareness about openscience.
A group of Kenyan OpenCon community members is working to understand how university students in Kenya are involved when it comes to Open Access, Open Education, and Open Data. If you have a few minutes, we would appreciate if you could support their efforts by filling out this short survey: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/MQZJ5NM

Any questions about the survey should be directed to Lillian Juma: lillianadhiambojuma@gmail.com.
